data.text:
Arnold Schwarzenegger

Profession: Actor, Body Builder and Governor of California

Biography: Austrian-born, becoming a naturalised US Citizen in 1983 Arnold Schwarzenegger won Mr Olympia 7 times.

A successful business man he became a film star in action films, including the Conan and Terminator series.

As a Republican he became Governor of California in 2003 and served 2 terms until 2011. Hasta la vista, baby.

Born: July 30, 1947

Birthplace: Thal, Austria

Age: 77 years old

Generation: Baby Boomer

Chinese Zodiac: Pig

Star Sign: Leo

Historical Events

Arnold Schwarzenegger becomes a US citizen

"The Terminator" directed by James Cameron, starring Arnold Schwarzenegger, Linda Hamilton and Michael Biehn is released in the US

"Terminator 2: Judgement Day" directed by James Cameron, starring Arnold Schwarzenegger, Linda Hamilton and Edward Furlong premieres at Century City, California

"Batman and Robin" directed by Joel Schumacher, starring George Clooney, Arnold Schwarzenegger and Chris O'Donnell premieres in Los Angeles

California holds gubernatorial recall election - Governor Gray Davis loses and actor Arnold Schwarzenegger becomes governor

California's Proposition 8, the ballot initiative prohibiting same-sex marriage passed by the state's voters in 2008, is overturned by Judge Vaughn Walker in the case Perry v. Schwarzenegger

Personal Life

Actor and body builder Arnold Schwarzenegger (39) weds American journalist and newscaster Maria Shriver (30); divorce in 2011

Journalist and executive producer Maria Shriver (55) divorces Hollywood action film icon Arnold Schwarzenegger (63) due to irreconcilable differences after 25 years of marriage
